An Air Force fighter jet based in Massachusetts crashed in the mountains of western Virginia today and officials said the pilot's fate remains unknown.

The crash shook the ground and frightened local residents in Western Virginia shortly before 9am this morning.

But no injuries were reported on the ground as authorities located the crash site through heavy smoke on a mountainside.

