Eyewitnesses reported an explosion-like noise just before 9 a.m., according to Augusta County dispatcher Becky Coynter.

Local resident Rebecca Shinaberry, 63, lives on a farm about two miles away.

She said: 'It's the loudest noise I've ever heard. [It] just shook the ground, and from my house we could just see a big plume of smoke.'

Deerfield is about 135 miles northwest of Richmond.

F-15s are maneuverable tactical fighters that can reach speeds up to 1,875 mph, according to the Air Force.

The F-15C Eagle entered the Air Force inventory in 1979 and costs nearly $30 million. The U.S. Air Force has nearly 250 of them.

